I’ve been coming here for years for their jerk chicken tips. This time, I wanted to try their jerk egg rolls. I’m lactose intolerant & didn’t know that they put cheese in their egg rolls. And there’s nothing explaining that on their menu. Typically, egg rolls don’t have cheese. Basic egg rolls have cabbage & whatever meat inside of them. After my 1st bite, I noticed the cheese & explained to the cashier that I can’t eat cheese. I was hoping that they’ll just exchange it seeing that I only took one bite & make me a fresh one without cheese. Her only response was “the owners not here & we don’t give refunds or exchanges”. And by the way, their egg rolls are meat & cheese only, wrapped in a deep fried tortilla so basically it’s a deep fried burrito.
